pullrequest.title: Raise TypeError rather than silently converting non-string keys in JSON encoding.

content.raw:
Looks ok \(haven’t tested in labscript software but did a quick check on the command line\).

P.S. I learned the other day that `assert` can be removed/ignored by a command line flag of `python.exe` that enables compiler optimisations. Was wondering if we should thus avoid using them \(I noticed there was one in this file which reminded me!\)
